  "prompt": "Who all can apply the title \"Er.\" as a prefix for their names?",
  "response": "The title \"Er.\" is typically used by Engineers in some countries, particularly in India. Here's a breakdown of who can use this prefix:\n\n1. Professional Engineers with a Bachelor's or Master's degree in Engineering, such as:\n- Civil Engineers\n- Mechanical Engineers\n- Electrical Engineers\n- Computer Engineers\n- Chemical Engineers\n- Electronics Engineers\n- Aerospace Engineers\n- And other engineering disciplines\n\n2. Requirements usually include:\n- Completing a 4-year engineering degree from a recognized university\n- Obtaining a degree from an accredited engineering program\n- Graduating with a B.E. (Bachelor of Engineering) or B.Tech (Bachelor of Technology) degree\n\n3. In some regions, additional criteria may include:\n- Registration with professional engineering bodies\n- Passing professional certification exams\n\nNote: The usage and acceptance of \"Er.\" can vary by country and region. In India, it's more commonly used, while in many other countries, engineers might use \"Eng.\" or simply state their specific engineering discipline.\n\nThe most important factor is having a legitimate engineering degree from a recognized institution.",
